<section class="diet-section" id="diet">
  <div class="section-label">Nutrition</div>
  <h2>Eating well for <em>lasting change</em></h2>
  <div class="diet-grid">
    <div class="diet-content">
      <p class="section-intro">There is no single diet that works for everyone. Our approach is evidence-based, sustainable, and personalised — not fad-driven.</p>
      <h3>Key dietary principles</h3>
      <div class="food-tips">
        <div class="food-tip">
          <div class="food-tip-icon">🥦</div>
          <div class="food-tip-text">
            <strong>Prioritise whole, unprocessed foods</strong>
            <span>Vegetables, legumes, whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats form the foundation of any effective eating plan.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="food-tip">
          <div class="food-tip-icon">⚖️</div>
          <div class="food-tip-text">
            <strong>Caloric deficit — done sustainably</strong>
            <span>A modest 500–750 kcal/day deficit produces 0.5–1 kg/week loss without triggering metabolic adaptation. Crash diets are counterproductive.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="food-tip">
          <div class="food-tip-icon">💧</div>
          <div class="food-tip-text">
            <strong>Hydration matters</strong>
            <span>Drinking water before meals reduces appetite. Aim for 8–10 glasses daily. Avoid sugar-sweetened beverages entirely.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="food-tip">
          <div class="food-tip-icon">🕐</div>
          <div class="food-tip-text">
            <strong>Meal timing and frequency</strong>
            <span>Regular meals prevent binge eating. Avoid eating after 8pm. Breakfast supports metabolic function throughout the day.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="diet-image-stack">
